<paragraph blockId="26.[166,794,1193,1304]" pageId="26" pageNumber="53">
<taxonomicName authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2007" box="[166,299,1194,1217]" class="Insecta" family="Canacidae" genus="Zalea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="earlyi">
<emphasis box="[166,299,1194,1217]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="53">Zalea earlyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles other 
<collectingCountry box="[490,636,1193,1216]" name="New Zealand" pageId="26" pageNumber="53">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
<taxonomicName box="[646,794,1193,1217]" class="Insecta" family="Canacidae" genus="Zalea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[646,707,1194,1217]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="53">Zalea</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
with prothoracic precoxal bridge (e.g., 
<emphasis box="[573,794,1223,1246]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="53">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Harrison" baseAuthorityYear="1976" box="[573,693,1223,1246]" class="Insecta" family="Canacidae" genus="Zalea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="horningi">Z. horningi</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2007" box="[702,794,1223,1246]" class="Insecta" family="Canacidae" genus="Zalea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="johnsi">Z. johnsi</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
etc.), but these all lack the well-developed set of postgenal setulae, and the females, where known, do not have tergite 7
</paragraph>
